<Layout title="work">
  <section>
    <h1>💼 Professional Experience</h1>
    <p>
      I've been programming on and off since about 2012, and went to college for
      computer science, graduating with my Bachelors of Science in Computer
      Science with a minor in Mathematics.
    </p>
    <p>
      During college, I interned with <a
        href="https://www.mavericksoftware.com/">Maverick Software</a
      > and was contracted out to <a href="https://tr.com">Thomson Reuters</a>,
      where I ended up with a full-time offer and joined in June of 2024. I work
      on several projects in my free-time to improve my professional experience,
      you can check those out on /projects.
    </p>

    <article class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl">Software Engineer @ Thomson Reuters</h2>
      <i>June 2024 - Present</i>

      <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
        <li>
          Converted legacy website code to conform to <a
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/standards-guidelines/wcag/">WCAG 2.0</a
          > through semantic and style changes.
        </li>
        <li>
          I started with working on Westlaw Precision and Gen AI-related API
